INSERT INTO `wpWPP_postmeta` VALUES (2332, 164, 'description', 'The Disney Vault was a term used to describe recently re-released classic Disney movies, so that they could be enjoyed by new audiences. I sought out to rebrand this experience, adding the flair of mystery and intrigue that the name suggests. Pulling direct inspiration from graphics found on older safes, as well as the ornamentation of the silver screen,  the visual language speaks to a new discovery of something quite old. The experience I have crafted reinforces this motif. The packaging of the individual dvd\'s found in the collection keep the identity of the movie a secret until it is opened, and the website; upon loading the user is prompted to blow of the "dust" on the screen before they can view the content.') ; 
